{"word":"H331 - אָטַם - ʼâṭam - aw-tam' - Narrow","slug":"H331","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Original: </strong><span class=\"hebrewOrGreek\">אָטַם</span>"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Transliteration: </strong>ʼâṭam"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Phonetic: </strong>aw-tam'"},{"paragraph":"<strong>Short Definition: </strong>Narrow"},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<b>&#x05D0;&#x05D8;&#x05DD; - 'a&#x0302;t&#x0323;am</b> - <i>aw-tam'</i><p/>A primitive root; to <i>close</i> (the lips or ears); by analogy to <i>contract</i> (a window by bevelled jambs): - narrow, shut, stop."},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<strong>Cognate:</strong> <a href=\"#/H330\">H330</a>"}]}